6.27.20  8:39 pm   So, I've been trying analyse the time signature(s) of "Movie Star". I think it's mostly a 3/4+6/4 additive meter instead of 9/4. Is that how you were counting/feeling it or am I wrong? I was thinking something like this:

  Intro:  4x (3/4+6/4)

Verse1:  2x (3/4+6/4) | 4x 3/4
Verse2:  2x (3/4+6/4) | 4x 3/4
Chorus1:  2x (3/4+6/4)

Verse3:  2x (3/4+6/4) | 4x 3/4
Verse4:  2x (3/4+6/4) | 3x 3/4 | 4/4
Chorus2:  2x (3/4+6/4)
Chorus3:  (3/4+6/4) | 3/4 | 4/4

Bridge:  3x 3/4 | 4/4 | 3x 3/4 | 4/4 | 4/4

Verse5:  2x (3/4+6/4) | 4x 3/4
Verse6:  2x (3/4+6/4) | 3x 3/4 | 4/4
Chorus4:  2x (3/4+6/4)
Chorus5:  2x (3/4+6/4)

  Outro:  5x (3/4+6/4)

      i was hearing the main figure as 4+5. the verse for me is:
      4+5, 4+5, 3+3, 4+2
      4+5, 4+5, 3+3, 4+2
      or:
      4+5, 4+5, 3+3, 4+2
      4+5, 4+5, 3+3, 4+3
     
      the bridge would be:
      3,3,4,3
      3,3,4...and however much is left
     
      all chorus/vamps are 4+5.
      as you've noted there is likely a quick exception when ditching into the bridge
